---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Custom GPT Management Setup - ULTRACTION';
const description = 'Configure the ULTRACTION Custom GPT to manage both jobs and news with one shared API key and one combined OpenAPI schema.';
---

<Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  image="/logo/UGC-HEADER.png"
  noIndex={true}
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background py-12 px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
      <header class="mb-10">
        <span class="eyebrow">Developer Guide</span>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-bold font-heading text-primary md:text-5xl">
          ULTRACTION GPT Manager Setup
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg text-primary/80">
          Configure one Custom GPT that can manage both recruitment and news publishing.
          The combined schema lives at <code>/api/openapi.yaml</code>, and protected actions
          accept the same key through either custom header name.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="surface-card mb-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="quick-card">
          <p class="quick-label">Import URL</p>
          <code class="quick-code">https://ultraction.ae/api/openapi.yaml</code>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-card">
          <p class="quick-label">Recommended Auth</p>
          <code class="quick-code">x-jobs-api-key</code>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-card">
          <p class="quick-label">Coverage</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary/75">Jobs CRUD and news CRUD in one GPT action schema.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="surface-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="section-title">What Changed</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="info-panel">
            <h3 class="panel-title">Unified key flow</h3>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              Protected jobs and news operations now accept the same key through
              <code>x-jobs-api-key</code> or <code>x-news-api-key</code>. Use one header globally in ChatGPT.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-panel">
            <h3 class="panel-title">Combined action schema</h3>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              <code>/api/openapi.yaml</code> now exposes a single management schema with both
              <code>/jobs</code> and <code>/news</code> operations under <code>https://ultraction.ae/api</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="surface-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="section-title">Environment</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          For a truly shared setup, define <code>ULTRACTION_API_KEY</code>. Existing deployments can
          also keep using service-specific keys with <code>JOBS_API_KEY</code> and <code>NEWS_API_KEY</code>.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block">ULTRACTION_API_KEY=your-shared-management-key
JOBS_API_KEY=optional-service-specific-override
NEWS_API_KEY=optional-service-specific-override</pre>
        <p class="note">
          If service-specific keys are set, they take precedence for their own endpoint. Otherwise the shared
          ULTRACTION key is used.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="surface-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="section-title">ChatGPT Configuration</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">1</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="panel-title">Create or open the GPT</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                In ChatGPT, open <strong>GPTs</strong>, create a new GPT, and switch to the
                <strong>Configure</strong> tab.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">2</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="panel-title">Set the instructions</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                Use the ULTRACTION Content & Recruitment Manager prompt from
                <code>PROMPT.md</code>, but keep the API key out of the instructions field.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">3</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="panel-title">Add the action schema</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                In <strong>Actions</strong>, import from URL:
              </p>
              <pre class="code-block compact">https://ultraction.ae/api/openapi.yaml</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">4</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="panel-title">Configure authentication</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                In the GPT authentication UI choose API-key auth with a custom header.
              </p>
              <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="info-panel">
                  <p class="quick-label">Recommended</p>
                  <pre class="code-block compact">Header: x-jobs-api-key
Value: your shared ULTRACTION key</pre>
                </div>
                <div class="info-panel">
                  <p class="quick-label">Alternative</p>
                  <pre class="code-block compact">Header: x-news-api-key
Value: same shared ULTRACTION key</pre>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">5</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="panel-title">Save and validate</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                Save the GPT, then test both domains from the same conversation to confirm the shared auth flow.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="surface-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="section-title">Validation Prompts</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"List all open jobs."</code></div>
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"Create a site engineer vacancy in Abu Dhabi with a full job description."</code></div>
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"Show the latest published news articles."</code></div>
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"Draft a news post about ULTRACTION winning a new infrastructure contract."</code></div>
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"Publish the most recent draft news article."</code></div>
          <div class="prompt-card"><code>"Archive the job titled Senior Planner."</code></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="surface-card">
        <h2 class="section-title">Operational Notes</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="info-panel">
            <h3 class="panel-title">Production-first schema</h3>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              The combined schema is anchored to <code>https://ultraction.ae/api</code> so direct GPT configuration
              can point to production without local tunneling.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-panel">
            <h3 class="panel-title">Backward compatibility</h3>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              Existing bearer-token clients and endpoint-specific headers continue to work, so this change does not
              break current admin or automation flows.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/careers-admin" class="text-accent underline transition-colors hover:text-accent/80">
            Careers admin
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .surface-card {
    background: hsl(var(--color-surface));
    border: 1px solid hsl(var(--color-border) / 0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    color: hsl(var(--color-accent));
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .section-title {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary));
    font-family: var(--font-heading, inherit);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .section-copy {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary) / 0.78);
  }

  .quick-card,
  .info-panel,
  .prompt-card {
    background: hsl(var(--color-card));
    border: 1px solid hsl(var(--color-border) / 0.3);
    border-radius: calc(var(--radius) * 0.8);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .quick-label {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-accent));
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .quick-code {
    display: block;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary));
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  .panel-title {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary));
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .panel-copy {
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary) / 0.74);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .code-block {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: calc(var(--radius) * 0.8);
    border: 1px solid hsl(var(--color-border) / 0.3);
    background: hsl(var(--color-card));
    padding: 1rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary) / 0.86);
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .code-block.compact {
    padding: 0.875rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .note {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary) / 0.6);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .step-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    height: 2.5rem;
    width: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: hsl(var(--color-accent));
    color: hsl(var(--color-card));
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .prompt-card code {
    color: hsl(var(--color-primary));
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
